&lt;/h2>&lt;p>&lt;a class="link" href="https://leetcode.com/problems/subsets/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
>Subsets&lt;/a>&lt;/p>
&lt;blockquote>
&lt;p>Given a set of distinct integers, nums, return all possible subsets (the power set).&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Note:&lt;/strong> The solution set must not contain duplicate subsets.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Example:&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-fallback" data-lang="fallback">&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;/blockquote>
&lt;p>Input: nums = [1,2,3]&lt;br>
Output:&lt;br>
[&lt;br>
[3],&lt;br>
[1],&lt;br>
[2],&lt;br>
[1,2,3],&lt;br>
[1,3],&lt;br>
[2,3],&lt;br>
[1,2],&lt;br>
[]&lt;br>
]&lt;/p>
